%% Classical GoF Chain of Responsibility — a linked list of handlers,
%% each deciding whether to handle the request or pass it along.
%% Rust's idiom is a vector of handlers (or a nested function chain
%% via the Tower/axum Layer pattern).
classDiagram
    class Handler {
        <<trait>>
        +handle(req, next) Response
    }
    class AuthLayer
    class LoggingLayer
    class RateLimit
    class Service {
        +call(req) Response
    }

    Handler <|.. AuthLayer
    Handler <|.. LoggingLayer
    Handler <|.. RateLimit

    AuthLayer --> LoggingLayer : next
    LoggingLayer --> RateLimit : next
    RateLimit --> Service : next

    note for Handler "Each handler decides:\n1) observe the request,\n2) call next.handle(req),\n3) observe the response,\n4) decide whether to short-circuit\n   (e.g., AuthLayer returns 401)."
